args: (I guess all the resolve in the world\ndon't mean squat when you don't know\nhow to execute on it.)
Er, so where do you wanna go, Helena?
Well, since you were kind enough to agree\nto this, I thought perhaps we might do\nwhatever YOU wanted to do.
Oh. Well, uh...maybe we start\nwith a walk, then?
(Well, hell. Now what do I do?)
How did I KNOW this would happen?
He doesn't have a clue where to take her.\nHe hasn't thought about this at all!

She asks him out in the expectation of
being swept off her dainty feet and all he
does is make her feel like the village fool?
Such villainy cannot go unrepaid!
Okay, when did you get here?\nAnd also WHY are you here?!
I couldn't well allow two lovely maidens\nlike yourselves to tromp about without a\nproper escort, now could I?
Also, I wanted to lend support to my\nfellow pursuer of love. First dates are\njust ever so stressful.
Your support's the last thing I need.
A-Addis?! What are you doing here?!
Pretty sure that's my line. Anyway,\nI could tell someone was watchin' us.\nso I came over to see what's what.
And what of your date, mmm?
Told her to wait by the fountain.
Wait, you ABANDONED your date? Addis,\nthat is NOT how a gentleman treats a lady!
Hey, this whole date thing was your idea\nin the first place. Now then, what are you\nall doin' here?
We were worried about you—and clearly\nwe were right to do so, because you aren't\neven talking to that poor girl!
Yeah, well, how am I supposed to know\nwhat to say? I ain't never done this before.
As an accomplished veteran in the war\nof love, perhaps you will allow me to\nshare a few of my battlefield secrets.
Now then! The key to a date is sensing\nyour partner's every whim and desire,\nthen responding accordingly.
For example, if you see her glance at\nsome small boutique, you immediately\nwhisk her inside! That manner of thing.
Yeah, I ain't much for...all that.
Look, I know it sounds hard to take the\nlead like Orion, but you don't have to\nmake it quite so difficult.
She'll be happy if you just listen to her\nand care about what she's saying.
The girl speaks sooth! Because, you see,\ntime spent with a lover is like honey...
For it turns even the most insipid of\nconversations into a treasured delight!
If you need good topics to talk about,\nyou could always discuss your future...
We ain't got a future. We got one date.
Don't be so quick to dismiss her!\nWho knows what fate has in store\nfor the two of you?
The only reason I agreed to this was\nbecause it would be one and done.
Figured it would go so badly,\nshe'd just give up without me\nhavin' to reject her outright.
So you're just gritting your teeth\nand enduring this? Yikes.

Look, if you want to get this over with,
I honestly think it would go faster if you
were just talking to each other and...
you know. Enjoying yourselves?
But I can't make that happen,\nand it ain't right to put that on her.
You take the WEIRDEST things seriously.\nJust like someone else we know...
If you're not even considering your date,\nthen how does this help anyone?
Hey, you know what? You're right.\nDunno why I've been so determined\nto fight this battle alone.
Thanks for openin' my eyes.\nI'd better get back to her.
You were gone a long time, Addis.\nIs everything all right?
Yeah, sorry about that. And, uh...\nWell, sorry if I made you uncomfortable.

I know I ain't exactly a sparklin'
conversationalist. Truth be told,
I don't got much experience with
this sorta thing.
And if we lay our cards on the table,\nI don't have a clue where to take you.
Oh, goodness! And here I am trying\nto put you in charge of everything.
Yeah, so maybe you can just tell me?\nAbout what you like, I mean.
Oh. Well... I like flowers, I guess?
Then we're goin' to a florist.
